texts.text: >The day of the festival...
W-W-Whaaa...?! What's going on?!
Is that the altar?
Yeah, holy crap! It's a mountain of seasonal foods...!
I've never seen anything like this!
Nana, hurry...!
I'm right behind you. Let's start with our prayers too, sweetie.
Oh, right!
These are the potatoes from our farm, so make sure they go on the altar.
And then we can say thank you to the gods.
Yeah!
Whoa...
This is way more than I expected.
It's like when I was little. Nothing like how it's been recently.
It's really going well this year then. I'm glad to see it.
You really don't mind? I mean, your Halloween event...
Of course! I'm way more interested in your hometown's festival anyways.
It's really nice. The air, the friendly atmosphere...
Yeah...
>The shrine is filled to capacity with visitors!
Why are there so many people here all of the sudden?!
Yo, I called them over.
I told them what kind of festival and celebration was goin' on.
And you got this many to show up?!
Yo, people today love stuff that makes them feel connected.
See?
A smartphone? Just what exactly...
What the...?!
>The Hare of Inaba is dumbfounded by what it sees on the screen!
These are all moon viewing photos?!
They're making dango... And there's some susuki grass!
Hm? Someone's offered their dorayaki!
And this is... A chestnut cake?
Oh, and these people are making rabbit-shaped dango!
Wait... Okonomiyaki?! Everyone's making weird offerings left and right!
I'm staggered by the thought everyone is putting into this...
>Everyone is celebrating in their own way...
>Their thoughts and prayers are being posted to social media sites.
The fire starter for the whole thing was this picture, yo!
It's our best work yet! Honey was blown away by it too!
Holy...! That's all pudding?!
>The Liberators are all smiling as they surround a mountain of pudding!
>The decorative susuki grass is dwarfed by its size.
Dango serves as an offering just because it looks like the moon...
But who makes something like this instead?!
*Laugh*
Yo, let's do some moon viewin' together!
And we can make an offerin' of our choice while we're at it!
Let everyone know and tag it as #ExtremeMoonViewing!
It'll pique peoples' interest and soon they'll be doin' it too.
Yo, it's an event that gives everyone a sense of connection.
Pretty pics, interestin' pics and some laughs along the way!
Everythin' folks on social media love to see and do.
Yo, it's trendin' way better than the Halloween greed machine.
W-wow...
>The Hare of Inaba looks away from the phone and to the shrine.
Did you see Megakin's super pudding?
Yeah, and the video with him and his friends eating it all was good too!
I made something too. A mini shiratama parfait!
The one you posted yesterday? I saw that. It looked really good!
We didn't have to go far to get here, but isn't this kinda lame?
I don't really get this whole god of fertility thing either...
But all those seasonal snacks are made from these pumpkins and chestnuts and stuff, right?
If someone doesn't make them, then you can't make those snacks.
Damn, you're right... We have to say that we're thankful!
Please make it so that I can keep enjoying your delicious bounty...!

*Chuckle*
You're so easy!
When I was your age, we would do something like this every year...
That takes me back... Tonight feels like it did back then...
Nana, are you crying?
Don't cry. I'll give you some of my dango...
Oh, no. You should eat it. And make sure to thank the gods for this bountiful harvest.
Eat right, sleep right and grow to be big and strong.
>People are gathering to offer their thanks for the fall harvest.

*Snicker*
This is great!
Thank you!
The gods are sure to hear about this!
The one that saved me...! And the others responsible for this harvest!
Can you see this...! Is it reaching all of you?!
We're all giving our thanks!
>The Hare of Inaba jumps and tumbles out of sheer joy...
Man, you're really a colorful little bunny.
All thanks to you, Megakin.
You knew that the ones glued to their phones would want to join in on this event.
Staying on the forefront of marketing through social media.
Well done.
Well, for now. It was a fairly new experience for everyone is all yo.
This ain't the end of it.
What do you mean...?
Do you remember what trended well last year around this time?
How about 6 months ago? 3 months?
Yo, no one does. These things come and go like the tide.
This is the same. It'll get washed away like everything else.
Ain't it a shame?
Indeed...
In time, the people who know anything about this event will pass.
Then it will be lost forever.
It may be unavoidable.
Which is why the time we're spending right now is so important.
Participating in this celebration and understanding its roots.
It may act as the seed for greater things to come.
Even if these rituals and festivals do become lost,
this season, the time spent here
may serve as a story to tell our descendants later on in life.
That today was a fun and memorable experience.
That this festival reminded them of the gods that they are tied to.
That it's important to remember every so often to think about the things you can't see or feel.
So it's not necessarily all for naught.
*Snicker*
Aight, let's pray that everyone else will sow their own seeds too.
Megakin...! We made it...!
Kazufumi, you're over there? I've helped myself to some dango, if you don't mind.
Oh, I see...
We should go get some before it all runs out then. Shall we?
Yeah. Newbie and the others are gonna eat it all if we don't hurry.
>Megakin and Kazufumi wade through the crowd in search of the others.
You must be the ones.
It has been a long time since so many were gathered here... Thank you.
Yo, did you just...?
Yes. I saw it too. They said...
>They look back but see no one there...
Yo, let's go...
Agreed.
Good evening, Megakin! This place is buzzing with people!
That post was on fire! Now's a good time to do a stream, don't you think?

Yo, good call. Time for an
emergency Megakin VIDEO!
